<chapter xml:id="ci-effect-size-power">
  <title>Quantifying effects and designing studies</title>
  
  <introduction>
    <p>
      This chapter covers confidence intervals, effect sizes, and statistical power.
    </p>
  </introduction>

  <section xml:id="confidence-intervals">
    <title>Confidence intervals</title>
    <p>
      Confidence intervals provide a range of plausible values for parameters.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section xml:id="effect-size">
    <title>Effect size</title>
    <p>
      Effect sizes quantify the magnitude of relationships or differences.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section xml:id="statistical-power">
    <title>Statistical power</title>
    <p>
      Statistical power is the probability of detecting an effect when it exists.
    </p>
  </section>
</chapter>
